title: Jacques Brunel (rugby union) - Wikipedia
snippet: Jacques Brunel (born 14 January 1954) is a French rugby union coach and former player. He was most recently the French national team head coach, having previously been assistant coach for his nation and had led the Italian national team between 2011 and 2016.

title: Jacques Brunel (rugby player) - Alchetron, the free social encyclopedia
snippet: Jacques Brunel (born 14 January 1954 in Courrensan, France) is a French rugby union former player. He is now an international coach, currently coaching the forwards at Bordeaux Bgles, haven previously been the head coach of the Italian national team.

title: Jacques Brunel: Profile, Biography, Personality Type | Boo
snippet: Born on January 14, 1954, in Toulouse, France, Brunel has had a long and illustrious career in the sport. As a player, he primarily played as a flanker for Grenoble and Pau in the French domestic leagues.
